Can we learn to have healthy relationships people who we disagree with? 
Social media can be so beautiful but some things about it scare me. A lot of what we see are logical representations of things we already agree with and demonizing images of things we disagree with. This is expanding the gap between us and making it harder and harder to connect with people who are different than us🤍

We may have different ideas of how to get there but in the end don’t we all just want safety, freedom and happiness with the people we love?

#peace #freedom #meaningful #originalsong
Get to You 🖤 I have to say, sometimes a song just feels special to me. This one has had that feeling since I wrote it. I really hope I get to share it with you soon!

This literally came to me in the shower and I ran to the studio half dry to catch the moment 😄
I recommend putting on headphones and closing your eyes to listen but the golden hour backdrop also feels like it fits perfectly if you’d rather watch. 

Does anyone else resonate with these lyrics? I feel like I can’t help but give my whole heart away sometimes and if I’m honest, that’s resulted in me being let down quite a bit in my life. 

Grateful for all of you though 🌻 thank you for letting me be myself and for connecting to me through this music

A bit about the new song idea that I posted yesterday 🤍 It meant a lot to me to see that it connected with many of you who go through the same thing

I am preparing to release this song on Canada day and am looking to collaborate with members of Indigenous communities across the country.
 
I am currently looking for:
 
-  Voice recordings from people within these communities who have stories about or requests from our country regarding: Indigenous culture, residential schools, cultural preservation, and/or reconciliation. Snippets of these recordings will be featured over an instrumental section of the track. 
-  Vocalists from Indigenous communities who are open to singing on this song in a style that is traditional to their heritage.
-  A non-for-profit organization that is having a positive impact on Indigenous communities across the country. I will be choosing one of these organizations to give 100% of the streaming proceeds to. 
 
Please feel free to get in touch or submit anonymous recordings to: 
info@jordanhartsound.com
 
Gratefully,
 
Jordan Hart

#canada #indigenouspride #everychildmatters #reconciliation #celebration

Check out this crazy artwork by @emilynschultz 🤩 To me, it represents the inherent connection between the human body and earth, therefore connecting all of us. Can’t wait to give this to you, this one means a lot to me.

The End is out now everywhere you listen to music! Thank you for all of the shares and kind words this morning!! 

We made this one to celebrate The End of an amazing summer 🤍

The End (Full Lyric Video) 

To me, this video represents an arrival. Among the craziness of the city, with hundreds of people’s individual pursuits and obligations, the narrator takes a moment to slow down and address the audience and to sing about coming together in a time when it’s so easy to feel isolated.

The chaotic feeling of the city in this video was made by filming each performance publicly in slow motion. (The bts footage is hilarious 😂)

This woman wrote “The End” with me. She also designed the artwork.
She’s also the most beautiful person I’ve ever met.

Life is good ♥️

Hope you’re having as much fun listening to the new song as we had making it for you!

Trying my best to express gratitude and keep that joy alive these day ☀️ so honoured to be a part of my community and to have an opportunity to make music for all of you. Hope you’re enjoying this new one 🤍

Thank you for helping me sell out the first three shows to end 2023!! 

These experiences have grown so much from when it was just me on a street corner but the essence has always felt the same. A lot of the people who I get to share the stage with have been telling me how much they love you as an audience. And it’s true, there is no one I’d rather do this for and with. You show up with both the ability to party AND the willingness to go to those deep vulnerable places together. You show respect for the musicians, the lyrics and each other. This thing is really starting to feel like family and I can’t wait to spread it around the world with you and because of you. Thank you from the bottom of my heart,

J

To parents young and old: Thank you for the personal work that you've done in your life to help your children not have to go through the same trauma that you went through in yours. Your own personal healing journey will have an effect on all of the generations that come from you. My Dad did so much to make sure that the world I grew up in was full of intentional love and support and it's had more of an impact on me than I can put into words. In the ways that you are still healing, I hope you can forgive yourself. Life is incredibly difficult at times but it's beautiful in it's imperfection. Light would mean so much less without darkness. Joy would mean so much less without suffering. The work you put into self love and healing is heroic and it has the power to change the world.

p.s. This song is called Til the Waters Dry. I've always heard the chorus with a full choir so I recorded one on top of this live performance 🫶🏻
